<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-21T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-21T03:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/934: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-21T15:00:00+07:00">June 21,
                                    1943—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 21—2:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>988. From Adler to Secretary of Treasury only. TF–133. Dr. Kung sent for
                            me on Saturday and asked if there had been any reply to the question
                            submitted to you in TF–128.<note n="83" xml:id="d390fn83">Telegram No.
                                879, June 9, 1 p.m., <ref target="#pg_457">p. 457</ref>.</note> When
                            I answered in the negative, he said he would appreciate receiving
                            Treasury’s response fairly soon, as unless some action is taken the
                            Agreement would expire at the end of the month. [Adler.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>